{{coord|38|12|51.414|N|139|26|22.108|E|region:JP_type:landmark|display=title}} {{infobox Onsen |Name = Senami Onsen |image = Senami spa taikanso 2008.jpg |Comment = An open‑air bath with a view of the {{ill|Sea of Japan|ja|日本海|12=draft|12=draft}} {{Infobox mapframe|zoom=12|frame-width=300|frame-latitude=38.225|frame-longitude=139.47}} |Location = {{ill|Niigata Prefecture|ja|新潟県|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Murakami|ja|村上市|12=draft|12=draft}}{{Location map|Japan Niigata Prefecture|relief=1|float=center|width=225}} |Access = By car: Approximately 11 minutes via the {{ill|National Route 345|ja|国道345号|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Niigata Prefectural Road No.3: Niigata-Shin-Hatsuta-Murakami Line|ja|新潟県道3号新潟新発田村上線|12=draft|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Japan Sea Tohoku Expressway|ja|日本海東北自動車道|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Murakami Senami Onsen Interchange|ja|村上瀬波温泉インターチェンジ|12=draft|12=draft}}; or 10 minutes by bus from the {{ill|Uetsu Main Line|ja|羽越本線|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Murakami Station|ja|村上駅|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="niigata-kankou">[https://niigata-kankou.or.jp/spot/11576 {{ill|Senami Onsen|ja|瀬波温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}] - Official Niigata Prefecture Tourism Information, Niigata Kankō Navi</ref> |Spring Quality = {{ill|Chloride Spring|ja|塩化物泉|12=draft|12=draft}} |Spring Temperature = |Yield = |pH = |Fluid Classification = |Osmotic Classification = |Number of Lodging Facilities = 11 |Total Capacity = |Annual Number of Bathers = |Statistical Year = |Notes = }} [[File:Kamome-dōri Street, Senami Onsen, Murakami, Niigata, Japan, October 2021.jpg|thumb|Kamome Street at {{ill|Senami Onsen|ja|瀬波温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}]] '''Senami Onsen''' (せなみおんせん) is a hot spring located along the coast of the {{ill|Sea of Japan|ja|日本海|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Niigata Prefecture|ja|新潟県|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Murakami|ja|村上市|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Spring Quality == * {{ill|Sodium Chloride Spring|ja|ナトリウム-塩化物泉|1=Brine spring|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name="Onsenn">[http://www.senami.or.jp/onsenn/#rekishi Introduction to the Spring] - {{ill|Senami Onsen Ryokan Cooperative Association|ja|瀬波温泉旅館協同組合|12=draft|12=draft}}. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref> ** Spring Temperature: 95℃<ref name="Onsenn"/>
== Hot Spring Town == [[File:Senami Beach 01.jpg|thumb|The view of the {{ill|Senami Coast|ja|瀬波海岸|12=draft|12=draft}} in front of the hot spring town]] The source water is a high‑temperature spring (approximately 100℃), also known as “Netsu no Yu.” In the onsen egg park, visitors can experience making {{ill|Onsen Tamago|ja|温泉玉子|12=draft|12=draft}} (hot spring eggs). Facing the {{ill|Sea of Japan|ja|日本海|12=draft|12=draft}} along the {{ill|Senami Coast|ja|瀬波海岸|12=draft|12=draft}}, there are a dozen or so {{ill|Ryokan|ja|旅館|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hotel|ja|ホテル|12=draft|12=draft}} establishments, as well as day‑use bath facilities and free foot baths. The sunset over the {{ill|Sea of Japan|ja|日本海|12=draft|12=draft}} is famous, and because the {{ill|Sanmen River|ja|三面川|12=draft|12=draft}} (locally pronounced “みおもてがわ”) flows through Murakami—and is renowned for the autumn upstream migration of {{ill|Salmon|ja|サケ|12=draft|12=draft}}—various inns serve local salmon dishes at dinner.
== History == The hot spring began in April 1904 (Meiji 37) when hot water erupted during oil exploration tests.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.sake3.com/contents5103/168|title=131 古写真に見る大正時代の瀬波温泉（1）|publisher={{ill|Murakami City Tourism Association|ja|村上市観光協会|12=draft|12=draft}}|accessdate=2022-11-06}}</ref>
In 1914 (Taishō 3), when the railway reached {{ill|Murakami Station|ja|村上駅|12=draft|12=draft}}, development accelerated and automobile services linking the station began.<ref name="Sake3-132">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.sake3.com/contents5103/169|title=132 古写真に見る大正時代の瀬波温泉（2）|publisher={{ill|Murakami City Tourism Association|ja|村上市観光協会|12=draft|12=draft}}|accessdate=2022-11-06}}</ref> At that time, as the hot spring was located in the area known as Matsuyama in Senami Town, it was locally called '''{{ill|Matsuyama Onsen|ja|松山温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}'''.<ref>{{Cite book|和書|author=鉄道省 編|date=1924|title=羽越線案内|publisher=鉄道省|id={{国立国会図書館書誌ID|000000595132}}|page=107}}</ref>
In 1937 (Shōwa 12), {{ill|Akiko Yosano|ja|与謝野晶子|12=draft|12=draft}} visited Senami Onsen and composed 45 poems.<ref name="Nippo160722">{{Cite news|url=https://www.hokurikushinkansen-navi.jp/pc/news/article.php?id=NEWS0000007726|title=Murakami Senami Onsen: Yosano’s 45 Poems Rekindle Light – A Map for a Poetic Monument Tour|publisher={{ill|Niigata Nippo|ja|新潟日報|12=draft|12=draft}}|date=2016-07-22}}</ref> In 1998 (Heisei 10), 45 poem monuments were installed in her honor.<ref name="Nippo160722"/><ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.senami.or.jp/kankou/#event|title=Yosano Akiko Poem Monument Tour Map|publisher={{ill|Senami Onsen Ryokan Cooperative Association|ja|瀬波温泉旅館協同組合|12=draft|12=draft}}|accessdate=2022-11-06}}</ref> For the 100th anniversary of the hot spring’s opening in 2004, a commemorative pocket park equipped with foot and hand baths was established.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Senami Onsen to Operate Tourist Buses for its 100th Anniversary|newspaper={{ill|日本経済新聞|ja|日本経済新聞|12=draft|12=draft}}|date=2004-02-25|page=22 (Local Economic Section, Niigata)}}</ref>
In 2009, a greenhouse utilizing hot spring waste heat was opened by a local company to cultivate tropical fruits such as {{ill|Passion Fruit|ja|パッションフルーツ|12=draft|12=draft}}, and it is operated as the Senami Nankoku Fruit Garden.
In 2021, a public bath ({{ill|Sento|ja|銭湯|12=draft|12=draft}}) utilizing the hot spring source was opened.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.niigata-nippo.co.jp/news/local/20210319605018.html|title=Couple from Osaka Opens a Public Bath, Creating a Daily Oasis at Murakami Senami Onsen|publisher={{ill|Niigata Nippo|ja|新潟日報|12=draft|12=draft}}|date=2021-03-19}}</ref>
== Access == * By Car: Approximately 11 minutes via the {{ill|National Route 345|ja|国道345号|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Niigata Prefectural Road No.3: Niigata-Shin-Hatsuta-Murakami Line|ja|新潟県道3号新潟新発田村上線|12=draft|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Japan Sea Tohoku Expressway|ja|日本海東北自動車道|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Murakami Senami Onsen Interchange|ja|村上瀬波温泉インターチェンジ|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="niigata-kankou" /></ref> * By Public Transportation: Alight at {{ill|Murakami Station|ja|村上駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Uetsu Main Line|ja|羽越本線|12=draft|12=draft}}; then take the “Senami Circular Bus”.<ref>[http://www.city.murakami.lg.jp/soshiki/13/senami-bus.html Senami Circular Bus] - Murakami City. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref> Alternatively, take a route bus operated by {{ill|Niigata Kotsu Tourism Bus|ja|新潟交通観光バス|12=draft|12=draft}} (bound for Matsukiwa/Iwafune); or use a shuttle bus provided by local accommodations (about 10 minutes).<ref>[http://www.niigata-kotsu.co.jp/~nk-kanko/murakami.html Murakami Area] - Niigata Kotsu Tourism Bus. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref> Additionally, a “Senami Onsen Direct Liner” operates from {{ill|Niigata Airport|ja|新潟空港|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>[http://www.niigata-airport.gr.jp/access/senami.php Senami Onsen Direct Liner (Niigata Airport ⇒ Senami Onsen)] - Niigata Airport. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref>
== Related Items == * {{ill|New Heartpia Niigata Senami|ja|ニューハートピア新潟瀬波|12=draft|12=draft}} – A hotel in Senami Onsen that was formerly known as {{ill|Kōsei Nenkin Senami Shiozaisō|ja|厚生年金瀬波しおざい荘|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kōsei Nenkin Heartpia|ja|厚生年金ハートピア|12=draft|12=draft}} Niigata Senami. * {{ill|Senami Coast|ja|瀬波海岸|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Sea of Japan Parkline|ja|日本海パークライン|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Murakami City Skate Park|ja|村上市スケートパーク|12=draft|12=draft}} – A skate park located in the hot spring town. * [http://www.senami.or.jp/senamin/ {{ill|Senamin|ja|せなみん|12=draft|12=draft}}] – The mascot inspired by the sunset at Senami Onsen. Its theme song “Ne, Senamin” was produced by the duo of lyricist [[みうらじゅん]] and composer [[サワサキヨシヒロ]].
