In 2009, a greenhouse utilizing hot spring waste heat was opened by a local company to cultivate tropical fruits such as {{ill|Passion Fruit|ja|パッションフルーツ|12=draft|12=draft}}, and it is operated as the Senami Nankoku Fruit Garden.
In 2021, a public bath ({{ill|Sento|ja|銭湯|12=draft|12=draft}}) utilizing the hot spring source was opened.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.niigata-nippo.co.jp/news/local/20210319605018.html|title=Couple from Osaka Opens a Public Bath, Creating a Daily Oasis at Murakami Senami Onsen|publisher={{ill|Niigata Nippo|ja|新潟日報|12=draft|12=draft}}|date=2021-03-19}}</ref>
== Access == * By Car: Approximately 11 minutes via the {{ill|National Route 345|ja|国道345号|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Niigata Prefectural Road No.3: Niigata-Shin-Hatsuta-Murakami Line|ja|新潟県道3号新潟新発田村上線|12=draft|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Japan Sea Tohoku Expressway|ja|日本海東北自動車道|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Murakami Senami Onsen Interchange|ja|村上瀬波温泉インターチェンジ|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="niigata-kankou" /></ref> * By Public Transportation: Alight at {{ill|Murakami Station|ja|村上駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Uetsu Main Line|ja|羽越本線|12=draft|12=draft}}; then take the “Senami Circular Bus”.<ref>[http://www.city.murakami.lg.jp/soshiki/13/senami-bus.html Senami Circular Bus] - Murakami City. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref> Alternatively, take a route bus operated by {{ill|Niigata Kotsu Tourism Bus|ja|新潟交通観光バス|12=draft|12=draft}} (bound for Matsukiwa/Iwafune); or use a shuttle bus provided by local accommodations (about 10 minutes).<ref>[http://www.niigata-kotsu.co.jp/~nk-kanko/murakami.html Murakami Area] - Niigata Kotsu Tourism Bus. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref> Additionally, a “Senami Onsen Direct Liner” operates from {{ill|Niigata Airport|ja|新潟空港|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>[http://www.niigata-airport.gr.jp/access/senami.php Senami Onsen Direct Liner (Niigata Airport ⇒ Senami Onsen)] - Niigata Airport. Accessed February 13, 2019.</ref>
== Related Items == * {{ill|New Heartpia Niigata Senami|ja|ニューハートピア新潟瀬波|12=draft|12=draft}} – A hotel in Senami Onsen that was formerly known as {{ill|Kōsei Nenkin Senami Shiozaisō|ja|厚生年金瀬波しおざい荘|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kōsei Nenkin Heartpia|ja|厚生年金ハートピア|12=draft|12=draft}} Niigata Senami. * {{ill|Senami Coast|ja|瀬波海岸|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Sea of Japan Parkline|ja|日本海パークライン|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Murakami City Skate Park|ja|村上市スケートパーク|12=draft|12=draft}} – A skate park located in the hot spring town. * [http://www.senami.or.jp/senamin/ {{ill|Senamin|ja|せなみん|12=draft|12=draft}}] – The mascot inspired by the sunset at Senami Onsen. Its theme song “Ne, Senamin” was produced by the duo of lyricist [[みうらじゅん]] and composer [[サワサキヨシヒロ]].
